Camera Pixel = Cixel
Camera Resolution = Rc
Light Pixel = Lixel
Light Resolution = Lc

Scene is composed of line segmenets Xi(t).
Xi(t),Ai,Bi € R^2
S={Xi(t)=Ai+t*(Bi-Ai),t€<0,1>}
k-Cixels center:
C(k)=(0,k), k € N, k>=0,k<Rc, P(k) € R^2
Center of camera projection (camera position)
C € R^2
k-Lixels center:
L(k)=L0+k/(Lc-1)*(L1-L0)
L(k), L0, L1 € R^2
Center of light projection (light position)
L € R^2




